We seem to have 3 nodeid loopups here: `contains(nodeid)`, `at(nodeid)`, `erase(nodeid)`.
I think we can reduce it to a single iterator lookup:
```suggestion
    if (auto it = m_peer_info.find(nodeid); it != m_peer_info.end()) {
        if (it->second.m_connection_info.m_wtxid_relay) m_num_wtxid_peers -= 1;
        m_peer_info.erase(it);
    }
````

